Halcyon Investments, a New Yorkinvestment partnership that deals mainly in risk arbitrage andstock trading, said it raised its Purolator Courier Corp staketo 726,700 shares, or 9.5 pct, from 474,900, or 6.2 pct.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,Halcyon, whose managing partner is Alan B. Slifka and Co, saidit bought 201,800 Purolator common shares between Feb 3 andMarch 2 at prices ranging from 28.689 to 34.811 dlrs each.    Halcyon, which said it has spent 20.1 mln dlrs for itsPurolator common shares, said it also acquired options on Feb27 giving it the right to buy 50,000 shares for 1.8 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;